            <title>[LUCENE-2809] IndexWriter.numDocs doesn&apos;t take into account applied but not flushed deletes</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-2809</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;The javadoc states that buffered deletes are not taken into account and so you must call commit first.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But, if you do that, and you&apos;re using CMS, and you&apos;re unlucky enough to have a background merge commit just after you call commit but before you call .numDocs, you can still get a wrong count back.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The fix is trivial &amp;#8211; numDocs should also consult any pooled readers for their current del count.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is causing an intermittent failure in the new TestNRTThreads.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
